# Firebase Configuration Example

This file shows the structure needed for Firebase configuration.
Copy this file to `js/firebase-config.js` and replace with your actual Firebase credentials.

```javascript
const firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
  authDomain: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.firebaseapp.com",
  projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
  storageBucket: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.appspot.com",
  messagingSenderId: "YOUR_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID",
  appId: "YOUR_APP_ID",
  measurementId: "YOUR_MEASUREMENT_ID"
};
```

## How to get Firebase credentials:

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/)
2. Select your project
3. Click on ⚙️ (Settings) → Project Settings
4. Scroll down to "Your apps"
5. Click on the Web icon (</>)
6. Copy the configuration values
